Dargaz

Dargaz (Persian: درگز‎, also Romanized as Dar Gaz; also known as Darreh Gaz; formerly, Moḩammadābād, Moḩammadābād Arbāb, and Muhammadābād) is a city in and the capital of Dargaz County, in Razavi Khorasan Province, Iran.

Surian

Abbas Abad (Tehran)

Abbās Ābād (Persian: عباس آباد - approximate latitude of 35°44'08"N and longitude of 51°26'08"E) is a large north-central neighborhood of Tehran, Iran, designated within the Seventh Municipal District of the capital.

Tiran, Iran

Tiran (Persian: تيران‎, also Romanized as Tīrān; also known as Tehrān, Tihrān, and Tirūn) is a city in and the capital of Tiran and Karvan County, Isfahan Province, Iran.

Temple of Anahita, Kangavar

The Anahita Temple (Persian: معبد آناهیتا or پرستشگاه‌ آناهیتا‎) is the name of one of two archaeological sites in Iran popularly thought to have been attributed to the ancient deity Anahita. The larger and more widely known of the two is located at…

Tehranpars

Tehranpars or Tehran Pars (تهران‌پارس) is an absorbed city inside the Greater Tehran Area where is located in north east of the city.

Takestan

Takestan (Persian: تاكستان‎, also Romanized as Tākestān and Tākistān; formerly, Seyādahan, Sīādehan, Sīahdehān, Siakh-Degen, and Siakhdekhan) is a city in and the capital of Takestan County, in Qazvin Province, Iran.

Shahr-e Babak County

Shahr-e Babak County (Persian: شهرستان شهر بابک‎) is a county in Kerman Province in Iran. The capital of the county is Shahr-e Babak. At the 2006 census, the county's population was 100,192 in 22,973 families. The county is subdivided into two distr…

Shahin Shahr

Shahin Shahr (Persian: شاهين شهر‎, also Romanized as Shāhīn Shahr) is a city in and the capital of Shahin Shahr and Meymeh County, Isfahan Province, Iran.

Sareyn

Sareyn (Persian: سرعين‎, also Romanized as Sar‘eyn, Sara’eyn, Sar‘eīn, Sar ‘Eyn, and Sarein) is a city in and the capital of Sareyn County, in Ardabil Province, Iran. Sareyn is known for its hot springs. The population is about 8000, and increases t…

Sarcheshmeh

Sarbaz

Salmas County

Salmas County (Persian: شهرستان سلماس‎) in kurdish Salvaz is a county in West Azarbaijan Province in Iran. The capital of the county is Salmas. At the 2006 census, the county's population was 180,708 . The county is subdivided into two districts: th…

Sahand University of Technology

Sahand University of Technology (SUT) (Persian: دانشگاه صنعتی سهند‎) is a leading engineering schools in Iran. Located in the northwest of Iran, 20 km southwest of Tabriz in Sahand satellite city, offering both undergraduate and postgraduate studies…

Saat Tower

Sa'at Tower also known as Tabriz Municipality Palace is the head office of the municipal government of Tabriz, the capital of East Azarbaijan Province, Iran.

Sa'adat Abad

Sa'adat Abad (Persian: سعادت آباد‎) is an affluent neighborhood located North of Shahrak-e Gharb. It is considered as one of the most upscale neighbourhoods of North Tehran. Kaj Square in Sa'adat Abad is famous for its large number of restaurants, y…

Osku County

Osku County (Persian: شهرستان اسکو‎) is a county in East Azerbaijan Province in Iran and in the vicinity of Tabriz. The capital of the county is Osku. Kandovan Touristy village is one of its subdivisions. Hilleh Historical Village is another histori…

Nur, Iran

Nur (Persian: نور‎, also Romanized as Nūr, Nour, and Noor; formerly, Sūldeh and Sūlehdeh) is a city in and capital of Nur County, Mazandaran Province, Iran.

Naqadeh

Naqadeh (Persian: نقده‎, also known as Nagadeh, Naghadeh, Naghdeh, and Nākhuda; formerly known as Suldüz (Persian: سولدوز), also Romanized as Sulduz, Solduz and Suldoz) is a city in and the capital of Naqadeh County, West Azerbaijan Province, Iran.

Mirjaveh

Mirjaveh (Persian: ميرجاوه‎, also Romanized as Mīrjāveh; also known as Mīrjāwa) is a town and the capital of Mirjaveh County, in Sistan and Baluchestan Province, Iran.

Karkheh Dam

The Karkheh Dam (Persian: سد کرخه‎) is a large multi-purpose earthen embankment dam built in Iran on the Karkheh River in 2001 by the Islamic Revolutionary Guards Corps (IRGC).

Jameh Mosque of Tabriz

The Jāmeh Mosque (Persian: مسجد جامع تبریز‎ - Masjid-e-Jāmeh Tabrīz) is a large, congregational mosque (Jāmeh) in Tabrīz city, within the East Azerbaijan Province of Iran. It is located in the Bazaar suburb of Tabriz next to the Grand Bazaar of Tabr…

Jameh Mosque of Nain
